# CRUD Module Generator

Para crear un nuevo módulo ("crear módulo [NOMBRE]" / "generate module [NOMBRE]") usar como referencia el módulo **Company** y este patrón.

## Estructura de archivos

Para entidad `[Entity]` (ej. Product, Branch):

```
src/modules/[entity]/
├── schema.ts
├── store/[entity]Store.ts
├── services/[Entity]Resource.ts
├── hooks/use[Entity]List.ts
├── components/[Entity]TableRow.tsx
├── [Entity]Form.tsx
├── [Entity]FormModal.tsx
├── [Entity]List.tsx
└── [Entity]ListPage.tsx
```

## Reemplazos de placeholders

| Placeholder | Sustituir por | Ejemplo |
|-------------|----------------|--------|
| [Entity] | PascalCase singular | Product |
| [entity] | camelCase singular | product |
| [Entities] | PascalCase plural | Products |
| [entities] | camelCase plural | products |

## Puntos clave por archivo

### schema.ts
- Zod schema (`[entity]FormSchema`), interfaz `I[Entity] extends IEntity`, tipo `[Entity]FormValues = z.infer<typeof schema>`.

### store/[entity]Store.ts
- `createEntityStore<I[Entity]>('[entity]')`.

### services/[Entity]Resource.ts
- `createCrudApi<I[Entity], [Entity]FormValues>({ basePath: '/[entity]' })`. Métodos: create, update, remove (no "save"); useBaseCrud recibe `resource: { save: Resource.create, update: Resource.update, delete: Resource.remove }`.

### hooks/use[Entity]List.ts
- `useBaseList<I[Entity]>({ store: use[Entity]Store, resource: [Entity]Resource, autoInit: true, initialSearch: { sort: [{ field: 'created_at', direction: 'desc' }] } })`.

### components/[Entity]TableRow.tsx
- Props: `IEntityTableRowProps<I[Entity]>` (entity, canEdit, canDelete, isLoading, isDeleting, isSaving, onEdit, onDelete).
- `memo` con comparador `checkMemoListProps`; `displayName = '[Entity]TableRow'`.
- ActionButtonGroup: `onEdit={canEdit ? () => onEdit(entity) : undefined}`, `onRemove={canDelete ? () => onDelete(entity) : undefined}`.

### [Entity]Form.tsx
- defaultValues con useMemo a partir de entity; useBaseCrud con save/update/delete; useForm con zodResolver; handleSubmit llama crud.submit(values) y onSuccess.

### [Entity]FormModal.tsx
- Props: `IEntityFormModalProps<I[Entity]>`. Footer: Cancelar + Submit (type="submit" form=FORM_ID). Modal envuelve [Entity]Form con formId, mode, entity, onSuccess.

### [Entity]List.tsx
- use[Entity]List() → onPageChanged, onRemove, onSearch, onReset, paramsSearch.
- use[Entity]Store() → entities, pagination, isLoading, isDeleting, isSaving (o selectores por campo si se quiere optimizar).
- useMultiplePermissions({ canCreate, canEdit, canDelete }).
- Handlers: handleCreate, handleEdit(**entity**), handleDeleteClick(**entity**) — parámetro es la entidad, no array.
- Tabla: `entities.map((entity) => <[Entity]TableRow key={entity.id} entity={entity} ... />)` — variable de bucle correcta.
- **Pagination**: `<Pagination pagination={pagination} onPageChanged={onPageChanged} />` (pagination es objeto con page, pages, total, per_page).
- ConfirmDialog: variant="delete", entityName={entityToDelete?.name}, isLoading={isDeleting}, onConfirm, onCancel.

### [Entity]ListPage.tsx
- Solo renderiza &lt;[Entity]List /&gt;.

## Después de crear el módulo

1. Ajustar schema y basePath al backend.
2. Añadir ruta en `App.tsx`: dentro de `PermissionRoute` si aplica, p. ej. `Route element={<PermissionRoute permissionEntity="[entity]" />}` con hijo `Route path="/[entity]" element={<[Entity]ListPage />} />`.
3. Añadir enlace en sidebar (`app-sidebar.tsx`) con el permiso correspondiente.
4. Verificar slugs de permisos (create.[entity], update.[entity], delete.[entity], read.[entity], report.[entity]) según backend.
